nodeSelector.description:
NodeSelector targets specific node pools or hardware characteristics.
Ensures workloads run only on nodes with matching labels.

Common use cases:
- GPU type selection: {"accelerator": "nvidia-t4"}
- Instance type: {"node.kubernetes.io/instance-type": "n1-highmem-8"}
- Dedicated encoding pool: {"workload-type": "video-encoding"}
- Hardware generation: {"cpu-generation": "skylake"}
- Storage tier: {"disk-type": "ssd", "iops": "high"}

Examples:
  {"accelerator": "nvidia-tesla-t4"} → NVIDIA T4 GPU nodes
  {"workload": "encoding", "priority": "high"} → High-priority encoding pool
  {"beta.kubernetes.io/instance-type": "c5.4xlarge"} → AWS compute-optimized

Node labels are set by cluster administrators or node provisioners.
